<title>USA: ALARIS sees more charges in second half.</title>
<headline>ALARIS sees more charges in second half.</headline>
<dateline>SAN DIEGO 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>ALARIS Medical Inc said Wednesday it expects about $4.5 million additional non- recurring integration charges during the second half of 1997 but no further charges after this year.</p>
<p>It also said it expects a return to profit in 1998 and expects 1998 to produce higher revenues than 1997, if &quot;present trends continue.&quot;</p>
<p>The company reported a second quarter loss of $0.12 per share compared with a profit of $0.06 for the same period a year ago.  The current quarter includes a $12 million charge for acquisition integration.</p>
